# Tugasnya adalah menjadikan 12 file .csv menjadi sebuah file .csv dengan menggunakan dataframe
#df = pd.read_csv("./Sales_Data/Sales_April_2019.csv")

files = [file for file in os.listdir('./Sales_Data')]

all_months_data = pd.DataFrame()

for file in files:
    df = pd.read_csv("./Sales_Data/"+file)
    all_months_data = pd.concat([all_months_data, df])

Task 4: Add a city column¶

In [60]:
def get_city(address):
    return address.split(',')[1]

def get_state(address):
    return address.split(',')[2].split(' ')[1]

#all_data['City'] = all_data['Purchase Address'].apply(lambda x: get_city(x) + '( ' + get_state(x) + ')') atau
all_data['City'] = all_data['Purchase Address'].apply(lambda x: f"{get_city(x)} ({get_state(x)})")

#Lambda x means the x value here is the cell content. 
#So we're saying for each of these cell contents we want to split it by commas and then grab the first index.
# kalau mw drop {all_data = all_data.drop(columns='nama kolom')}

Visualization of plot chart shows that the average of visitors are:

  • Peaks at around 11am and another peak at 7pm. Kinda make sense, maybe 11am is a lunch time and 7pm after work
  • If we gonna advertise effectively, I would say right before 11am or 6pm. Would be a good time of the peaks when all the orders in our data set happened

My recommendation is around 11am (11) or 7pm (19)

Question 4: What products are most often sold together?¶

In [68]:
#if they've the same order ID, that means those products are sold in a same time

#first we want to know all the spots in data frame
df = all_data[all_data['Order ID'].duplicated(keep=False)]
# click false and Shift+Tab, you will know the cuntion. Keep is basically is to keep all duplicate
# now we're going to group it together

df['Grouped'] = df.groupby('Order ID')['Product'].transform(lambda x: ','.join(x))

df = df[['Order ID', 'Grouped']].drop_duplicates()

df.head()

# we need to count the pairs

# Referenced: https://stackoverflow.com/question/52195887/counting-unique-pairs-of-numbers-into-a-python-dictionary
from itertools import combinations
from collections import Counter

count = Counter()

for row in df['Grouped']:
    row_list = row.split(',')
    count.update(Counter(combinations(row_list, 2)))
    
#count.most_common(10)
for key, value in count.most_common(10):
    print(key, value)

  • AAA Batteries (4-pack) is sold the most than others, the product has second lowest prices from all the product
